<TITLE> Somali Islamist head rejects UN-sponsored pact </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NAIROBI, Tue Jun 10, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - A hardline Islamist leader rejected on Tuesday a peace agreement brokered by the United Nations in Djibouti between the Somali government and some opposition figures. "We don't see that as a peace deal, we see it as a trap," Sheikh Hassan Dahir Aweys told Reuters by phone from Eritrea. "We encourage the insurgents and the Somali people not to be tired of combating the enemy.
